            <title>[SPARK-23976] UTF8String.concat() or ByteArray.concat() may allocate shorter structure.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-23976</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When the three inputs has `0x7FFF_FF00`, `0x7FFF_FF00`, and `0xE00`, the current algorithm allocate the result structure with 0x1000 length due to integer sum overflow.&lt;/p&gt;

